          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(center)">
                                        <placeName>St Thomas</placeName>
                                        <date>1 Nov 1847</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <placeName>Phila</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">I recd your few lines [?]<lb/> late with the
                                        Occident for <date>Oct</date> I thank<lb/> you for inserting
                                        our affairs. The <date>Sep</date> No I<lb/> have not
                                        recd.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">On <date>Sunday</date> evening a Young man of<lb/>
                                        our Congregation born at <placeName>St Croix</placeName> was
                                        baptized<lb/> by the <persName>Revd Mr Brett</persName> a
                                        Dutch Reformed Minister<lb/> the parents of this Young man
                                        completely neglected<lb/> his Religious education, he was
                                        but twice in<lb/> our Synagogue, never adhering to any of
                                        our<lb/> forms publicly defamed the day of
                                                  <date>Kipur</date> by<lb/> going to business, as
                                        soon as I heard that he<lb/> was so inclined I used my
                                        evidences[?] to prevent<lb/> him but he would not give me a
                                        hearing. The<lb/> consequence is in happiness to his family
                                        which they<lb/> richly merit—This <persName>Mr
                                                  Brett</persName> is pursuing<lb/>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>a line of conduct that requires our utmost<lb/> vigilance to stem.
                                        he seduces our lads<lb/> of 13 to 15 Years to become
                                        teachers to his<lb/> Sunday School, he has now two with
                                        him<lb/> teaching the negro children, the Catechisms<lb/>
                                        the Parent of one never sends him to our school<lb/> altho
                                        warned to do so, the other came to <del>our</del><lb/>
                                        school because his attendance was irregular<lb/> his conduct
                                        what it should not be was admonished, he was<lb/> permitted
                                        by those in whose care he is to Keep away—do me the favor to
                                        put in your paper<lb/> an article of warning to parents
                                        guardians<lb/> setting forth what they have to answer for
                                        by<lb/> the neglect of giving their children a
                                        Religious<lb/> education causing them to attend the
                                        Synagogue<lb/> make it strong as coming from you; for I
                                        fear<lb/> that unless something is done to arouse their<lb/>
                                        feelings we will have repetitions of what has<lb/> passed,
                                        for <persName>Mr Brett</persName> has very very
                                        persuasive<lb/> [?].</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">My daughter will be married this day</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>week.–With best wishes I am yr Truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <persName role="author">A Wolff</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>don't forget my [?] [?], [?]<lb/> please in the article to urge
                                        Parents guardians<lb/> of children to send them to school,
                                        many from<lb/> private [?] c. Do not send, point out<lb/>
                                        the impropriety</p>
                              <p>On <date>Sabath</date> M[?] of Tabernacle 7 of our young<lb/>
                                        people were confirmed by <persName>Mr Carillar[?]</persName>
                                        the<lb/> Ceremony was very impressive below the names<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mrs Daniel Wolff</persName>, <persName>Misses
                                                  Miriam</persName>
                                        <persName>Rebecca Wolff</persName><lb/>
                                        <persName>Miss D. Contessios[?]</persName>, <persName>Miss
                                                  DeMya</persName>
                                        <persName>Mr Alexander<lb/> Wolff</persName>
                                        <persName>Mr Jacob Benjamin</persName></p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Phila.</placeName>
                              </p>
